        "agreements": [
            "The main paper (Result 1) and its companion (Result 2) are highly relevant, as they directly address the emission line diagnostic methods for identifying AGN in dwarf galaxies.",
            "Several results (4, 6) highlight the limitations of mid-infrared color selection methods, supporting the main paper's argument for optimized optical diagnostics.",
            "Multiwavelength approaches, including mid-infrared data and variability, provide complementary insights and validation for AGN identification in dwarf galaxies."
        ],
        "disagreements": [
            "There is some disagreement on the relevance of results focused on high-redshift AGN (3) or general AGN classification (7), as they diverge from the main paper's focus on nearby dwarf galaxies.",
            "The evaluations differ in their assessment of the variability-based studies (9, 10), with Deepseek considering them more relevant than Claude."
        ],
        "key_insights": [
            "The main paper's methodology and findings are reinforced by multiple complementary studies (1, 2, 5) using the same RESOLVE/ECO surveys and multi-diagnostic approaches.",
            "Mid-infrared color selection methods have limitations, as highlighted by several results (4, 6), emphasizing the need for the main paper's optimized optical diagnostics.",
            "Variability-based studies (9, 10) provide an alternative perspective on AGN identification in dwarf galaxies, although they differ methodologically from the main paper's emission line diagnostics."
        ],
        "suggested_focus": [
            "Discuss the relevance and potential insights from high-redshift or general AGN classification studies in the context of the main paper's focus on nearby dwarf galaxies.",
            "Explore the potential synergies between the main paper's optical diagnostics and the variability-based methods, as well as their respective strengths and limitations.",
            "Address the overlap and mismatch between optical emission line diagnostics and mid-infrared color selection methods for identifying AGN in dwarf galaxies."
        ]
    }
}
